	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'd say yes. If the CPU is on, then so is the PPU. I am not aware of anyway that the PPU can be paused by a pin or whatever. When you say power-up sequence I assume you mean the reset that the 6502 must do to use the Reset Vector. As for anything before that, then I assume the same. We need Kevin Norton or Brad Taylor to do a check for us (hint, hint).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


